# Your rule content

1. Set Up the Project
+  Initialize the project and create the required directory structure.
+  Git Setup:
   ++ A GitHub repository has already been created at git@github.com:ekrown-dev/web-app.git
   ++ After initializing the project, sync with GitHub using:
	echo "# website development" >> README.md
	git init
	git add README.md
	git commit -m "first commit"
	git branch -M main
	git remote add origin git@github.com:ekrown-dev/web-app.git
	git push -u origin main

2. Frontend Setup (Next.js with TailwindCSS)
+  Use Next.js for a responsive frontend.
+  Set up TailwindCSS for styling.
+  Create reusable UI components (Navbar, ServiceCards, Testimonials, ContactForm).
+  Use 'public/' images provided for website background, hero section and logo.   

3. Backend Setup (Express.js with Node.js)
+  Use Express.js with cors and dotenv.
+  Define API routes for services, team members, and contact form submissions.

4. Setup a supabase local database as backend database
+  Use supabase CLI with npx
+  When a new migration is created, create table(s) to hold the data
+  Add seed data in 'supabase/seed.sql' file
+  Reset supabase database everything is done
+  Use 'npx' to run the commands.

5. Git Ignore Sensitive Files
+  Before committing, ensure sensitive files are NOT tracked:
   ++ Create a .gitignore file and add, for examples:
	node_modules/
	.env
	.next/
	__pycache__/
	etc.
++  Ensure .env is used for storing secrets (e.g., database credentials).

